rComments: Took the class because it filled LibEds but ended up really liking it. He is very knowledgeable and an entertaining lecturer even when the material was dry. He has a way with words that makes him easy to listen to. The class was very easy, the readings are absolutely not mandatory, If you stay awake during class you'll do well. Strongly recommend.

Teaches course as if it's a 4th-yr or graduate course. Has no concept of how to teach concepts clearly,from the beginning. Assumes you have knowledge of advanced philosophical concepts. Tests not reflective of text/class (seemed to be based on some different book). After 1st midterm, at least 100-120 dropped the course, as confirmed by prof himself
